<h2>About</h2>

<p>
Lex is a tokeniser - a program that takes a character stream and outputs
a stream of tokens. Yacc “parses” this stream of tokens and converts it into
a meaningful grammar. Lex and Yacc are useful for the construction of
interpreters, compilers and other processors of semi-natural languages.
</p>

<p>
This presentation will introduce both of these tools using their
<a href="http://www.perl.org/">Perl</a> implementations.
</p>
